&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northamptonshire Healthcare NHS foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Study Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mainly Monday – Friday but occasional weekends/evenings expected&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full- time 37.5 hours a week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Research and Innovation team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Innovation and Research Team at Northamptonshire Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust are looking for an enthusiastic Band 3 Research Study Administrator to work as part of the Research Delivery Team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The team specialise in the set up and delivery of National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) portfolio research studies, including clinical trials to patients and carers within the county across a portfolio of areas. This includes but is not limited to dementia, mental health and community services. The post holder will work closely with clinical and administrative staff within the team, other NHFT services and the NIHR Clinical Research Network East Midlands (CRN EM).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must demonstrate excellent verbal and written communication skills, be enthusiastic, motivated and a good team player, with a flexible attitude to work. You will be expected to be IT literate and confident in the use of Microsoft Office and web based applications. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post is based at Berrywood Hospital, Northampton, but regular travel across Northamptonshire and the CRN EM region will be required, access to a car is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liz Sabin – Senior Clinical Research Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elizabeth.Sabin@nhft.nhs.uk tel 07770 728416&lt;/p&gt;
